PROBLEM STATEMENT

Manufacturers receive large volumes of customer complaints related to product quality and performance. Manually summarizing and categorizing complaints for analysis is labor-intensive and inconsistent, delaying response and corrective actions. Quality and customer service teams need concise, standardized summaries to identify common issues and prioritize improvements. Existing CRM and complaint management systems lack Al-powered summarization features integrated with manufacturing defect data. Without automation, opportunities to enhance product quality and customer satisfaction are missed, impacting brand reputation and revenue.

Data Considerations:

Unstructured customer complaint texts from CRM systems in text or JSON formats; access to product defect databases; APIs for data retrieval and updates; historical complaint summaries for prompt tuning; synthetic complaint texts for varied scenarios; data privacy adherence for customer info; preprocessing to clean text and anonymize sensitive data.

Consider using synthetic or anonymized data where appropriate. Ensure data quality and relevance to the problem context.

SOLUTION EXPECTATIONS

A web-based Al tool where users upload or query complaint texts and receive Al-generated summaries and categorizations; editing interface for quality control; integration with CRM and quality APIs for data exchange; export options to PDF/CSV; KPIs include summarization accuracy and time saved; demo with sample complaint data and summary generation workflow.

Feel free to explore creative solutions that align with the problem context and objectives.
